Model.Name: Disc_CF_Model
Model.Notes: Calculates present value of all cashflows for conventional business

Input.Name: Benefit
Input.Notes: Inputs related to benefits under policy

Input.Name: PRM_PA
Input.Notes: Annual premium amount. For single premiums this is the single premium, for all other premium frequencies this is the annual premium.

Input.Name: PRODUCT
Input.Notes: Product Type: Term insurance (TERM), Whole of life assurance (WOL), Pure Endowment (PURE_ENDOW), Endowment (ENDOW)

Input.Name: SA_INST
Input.Notes: Death benefit sum assured, ie the amount of life cover provided, at policy commencement

Input.Name: SA_LS
Input.Notes: Death benefit sum assured, ie the amount of life cover provided, at policy commencement

Input.Name: SA_TR
Input.Notes: Death benefit sum assured, ie the amount of life cover provided, at policy commencement

Parameter.Name: CalcBasis_w
Parameter.Notes: Set within code to Reserve or Pricing

Parameter.Name: PremTerm_w
Parameter.Notes: Premium paying term (in months) calculated in code for WOL plans and set to Input PremTerm * 12 otherwise

Parameter.Name: SM_Mortality_Life1
Parameter.Notes: Mortality submodel used to calculate mortality for life 1

Parameter.Name: Tbl_Exp
Parameter.Notes: Expense basis table, varies by Product and CalcBasis_w (Reserve or Pricing)

Parameter.Name: Term_w
Parameter.Notes: Term of policy (in months) calculated in code for WOL product. For other products set to Input Term * 12 but restricted in code to the month in which the appropriate lives die.

Parameter.Name: ValIntMaxRows_w
Parameter.Notes: Last row for which there are values in the valuation interest rate table

Formula.Name: AccDeathBenAnn
Formula.Value: Return InitDeathBenAnnPP() * DTH_INST_M * FreeCovExGrat(t) * NumAccDeaths(t)

Formula.Name: AccDeathBenLS
Formula.Value: Return SA_LS * FreeCovExGrat(t) * NumAccDeaths(t)

Formula.Name: AccDeathBenTR
Formula.Value: Return SA_TR * FreeCovExGrat(t) * NumAccDeaths(t)

Formula.Name: AccDthBenTotal
Formula.Notes: Total death benefit claims paid at the end of month t on both premium paying and paid up policies
Formula.Value: Return AccDeathBenLS(t) + AccDeathBenAnn(t) + AccDeathBenTR(t)

Formula.Name: AccDthBen_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
'Present Value at the end of month t of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (AccDthBen_PV_e(t + 1) + AccDthBenTotal(t+1) ) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: AccProbBirthWOP
Formula.Value: If PropIF_e(t) = 0 Or DurIF(t) > Term_w Then Return 0 Else Return Tbl_BirthsAccmWOP.Value(DurIF(t), "Accum_WOP") End If

Formula.Name: ActAnnInflRate
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ACT_INFL = 1 And ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 1 Else If IVP(t) = 1 And ACT_INFL = 1 Then If RUN_TYPE = "OPN" Then Return ActAnnInflRate(t - 1) * Tbl_CPI.Value(ValMnth(t), START_DT) Else If RUN_TYPE = "CLS" Then Return ActAnnInflRate(t - 1) * Tbl_CPI.Value(ValMnth(t), VALN_DT) End If End If End If End If

Formula.Name: AnnInflRate
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then Return (1 + RFRAnnNom(t)) / (1 + RFRAnnReal(t)) - 1 End If

Formula.Name: AnnRIRate
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then Return Math.Min(RIPrmRate(t) * (1 + (UW_LOAD_PC / 100)) * (RPR_PROPQ_PC / 100), 1) Else Return 0 End If

Formula.Name: BalDate
Formula.Value: '<Attributes(CalcOnce:=True)> Return GetBalDate(t - PeriodIF, ValDate, StepsPY)

Formula.Name: CFEoM
Formula.Value: Return NatDthBenTotal(t) + AccDthBenTotal(t) + NBWOPBen(t) - PremIncPPIF(t) - PremRecovery(t)

Formula.Name: CFSoM
Formula.Value: Return InitExp(t) + ExpClaims(t) + RenExpTotal(t)

Formula.Name: CancelRate
Formula.Value: Return Math.Min(1, Tbl_Cnl.Value(Math.Min(DurIF(t), Tbl_Cnl.Rows-1), SM_Mortality_Life1.RF_RSK) / 100)

Formula.Name: CancelRateFinal
Formula.Value:
If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return Math.Min(1, Math.Min(1 - LapseRateFinal(t) - NTURateFinal(t), CancelRate(t) * SeasonalCancelAdj(t) * (1 + LPS_STRESS_PC / 100)))

Formula.Name: DiscFac_mnth
Formula.Notes: Monthly discount factor appropriate during month t
Formula.Value:
'Assume no discounting applies before valuation date If t <= PeriodIF() Then Return 1
'Lookup annual interest rate (use last rate for period > end of table) and calculate monthly discount factor Return 1 / ((1 + RFRAnnNom(t)) ^ (1 / 12))

Formula.Name: DthBenTotal
Formula.Notes: Total death benefit claims paid at the end of month t on both premium paying and paid up policies
Formula.Value: Return SA_LS + SA_INST + SA_TR

Formula.Name: DurIF
Formula.Value: If ValMnth(t) >= 0 and (PeriodIF() + ValMnth(t)) <= Term_w Then Return PeriodIF() + ValMnth(t) End If

Formula.Name: ExpAcq
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return PremIncPPAdj(t) * REA_PRM_PC / 100 End If End If

Formula.Name: ExpClaims
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return ((CE_FIXED * ExpInflAdj(t) + CE_CLM_PC * DthBenTotal()) * FreeCovExGrat(t)) * (NumNatDeaths(t) + NumAccDeaths(t)) End If End If

Formula.Name: ExpInflAdj
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 1 Else If ValDate.AddMonths(ValMnth(t)).Month <> 2 Then Return ExpInflAdj(t - 1) Else Return InflAdjIndex(t) End If End If

Formula.Name: ExpPremRec
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return PremIncPPAdj(t) * REC_PRM_PC / 100 End If End If

Formula.Name: ExpRenMain
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return RE_FIXED / 12 * ExpInflAdj(t - 1) + PremIncPPAdj(t) * REM_PRM_PC / 100 End If End If

Formula.Name: FreeCovExGrat
Formula.Value: If DurIF(t) = 1 Then Return EX_GRAT_M + 1 Else Return 1 End If

Formula.Name: I17ExpClaims
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return (ExpClaims(t) + ExpPremRec(t)) * (NumNatDeaths(t) + NumAccDeaths(t)) End If End If

Formula.Name: I17InitExp
Formula.Value: If DurIF(t) = 1 Then Return (ExpAcq(t) + InitExp(t)) * PropIF_e(t) Else Return 0 End If

Formula.Name: I17RenExpTotal
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return (ExpRenMain(t)) * PropIF_e(t - 1) End If End If

Formula.Name: IVP
Formula.Value: If Date.FromOADate(BalDate(t)) <= ValDate.AddMonths(12) Then Return 1 Else Return 0 End If

Formula.Name: InflAdjIndex
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 1 Else Return InflAdjIndex(t - 1) * (1 + InflFac_mnth(t)) End If End If

Formula.Name: InflFac_mnth
Formula.Notes: Monthly discount factor appropriate during month t
Formula.Value:
'Assume no discounting applies before valuation date If t <= PeriodIF() Then Return 1 End If
If t < Term_w Then Return (1 + AnnInflRate(t)) ^ (1 / 12) - 1 End If

Formula.Name: InitDeathBenAnnPP
Formula.Value: Return Math.Round(SA_INST / DTH_INST_M, 2)

Formula.Name: InitExp
Formula.Value: If DurIF(t) = 1 Then Return (IE_FIXED * ExpInflAdj(t) + PremIncPPAdj(t) * (IE_PRM_PC / 100)) * PropIF_e(t) Else Return 0 End If

Formula.Name: LapseRate
Formula.Value: Return Math.Min(1, Tbl_Lps.Value(Math.Min(DurIF(t),Tbl_Lps.Rows-1), SM_Mortality_Life1.RF_RSK) / 100)

Formula.Name: LapseRateFinal
Formula.Value:
If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return Math.Min(1, LapseRate(t) * SeasonalLapseAdj(t) * (1 + LPS_STRESS_PC / 100))

Formula.Name: NBPremWOP_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
'Present Value at the end of month t of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (NBPremWOP_PV_e(t + 1) + NBWOPBen(t+1) ) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: NBWOPBen
Formula.Value: Return PremIncPPAdj(t) * NumNewBornWOP(t)

Formula.Name: NTURate
Formula.Value: Return Math.Min(1, Tbl_NTU.Value(Math.Min(DurIF(t), Tbl_NTU.Rows-1), SM_Mortality_Life1.RF_RSK) / 100)

Formula.Name: NTURateFinal
Formula.Value:
If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return Math.Min(1, NTURate(t) * (1 + LPS_STRESS_PC / 100))

Formula.Name: NatDeathBenAnn
Formula.Value: Return InitDeathBenAnnPP() * DTH_INST_M * FreeCovExGrat(t) * NumNatDeaths(t)

Formula.Name: NatDeathBenLS
Formula.Value: Return SA_LS * FreeCovExGrat(t) * NumNatDeaths(t)

Formula.Name: NatDeathBenTR
Formula.Value: Return SA_TR * FreeCovExGrat(t) * NumNatDeaths(t)

Formula.Name: NatDthBenTotal
Formula.Notes: Total death benefit claims paid at the end of month t on both premium paying and paid up policies
Formula.Value: Return NatDeathBenLS(t) + NatDeathBenAnn(t) + NatDeathBenTR(t)

Formula.Name: NatDthBen_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
'Present Value at the end of month t of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (NatDthBen_PV_e(t + 1) + NatDthBenTotal(t+1)) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: Net_Res_e
Formula.Value:
'Calculate Net reserve at the end of month t
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return Res_e(t) + RIPrem_PV_e(t) - RIClaimRec_PV_e(t)

Formula.Name: NumAccDeaths
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return PropIF_e(t - 1) * SM_Mortality_Life1.AccMortRateFinalMth(t)

Formula.Name: NumCancels
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return PropIF_e(t - 1) * CancelRateFinal(t)

Formula.Name: NumLapses
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return PropIF_e(t - 1) * LapseRateFinal(t)

Formula.Name: NumNTU
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return PropIF_e(t - 1) * NTURateFinal(t)

Formula.Name: NumNatDeaths
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return PropIF_e(t - 1) * SM_Mortality_Life1.NatMortRateFinalMth(t)

Formula.Name: NumNewBornWOP
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 0
Return PropIF_e(t) * AccProbBirthWOP(t)

Formula.Name: PeriodIF
Formula.Notes: Complete months from policy commencement date to valuation date
Formula.Value:
'Number of complete months from policy commencement to valuation date
'MsgBox("INCPT_DT = " & INCPT_DT & vbCrLf & "ValDate = " &ValDate)
Return DateSpan.TermInMonths(INCPT_DT, ValDate) 'Return DateSpan.TermInMonths(INCPT_DT, INCPT_DT)

Formula.Name: Pol_Year
Formula.Notes: Policy year
Formula.Value: 'Policy year, ie first 12 months from policy commencement = Pol_Year 1, next 12 months = Pol_Year 2 Return CInt(Fix((t + 11) / 12))

Formula.Name: PremIncPP
Formula.Value: Return PRM_PA / 12

Formula.Name: PremIncPPAdj
Formula.Value: Return PremIncPP() * (PremiumCollectPC(t) / 100)

Formula.Name: PremIncPPIF
Formula.Value: Return PremIncPPAdj(t) * PropIF_e(t)

Formula.Name: PremRec_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
'Present Value at the end of month t of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (PremRec_PV_e(t + 1) + PremRecovery(t+1) ) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: PremRecovery
Formula.Value:
Dim NonDeathExit As Double
NonDeathExit = LapseRateFinal(t) + CancelRateFinal(t) + NTURateFinal(t)
If NonDeathExit = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return (((NumNatDeaths(t) + NumAccDeaths(t)) * LapseRateFinal(t)) / NonDeathExit) * PremIncPP() End If

Formula.Name: Prem_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) for all premiums paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
'Present Value at the end of month t of all premiums paid from month t+1 onwards If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (Prem_PV_e(t + 1) + PremIncPPIF(t + 1)) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: PremiumCollectPC
Formula.Value:
Dim x As Double
If t <= PeriodIF() Or t >= Term_w - 4 Then Return 0 End If
If DurIF(t) = 1 Then x = NumCancels(t) Else x = 0 End If
If PropIF_e(t + 4) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return 100 - (NumLapses(t+1) + NumLapses(t + 2) + NumLapses(t + 3) + NumLapses(t + 4) * (PRM_4_PC / 100) - x) * (100 / PropIF_e(t)) End If

Formula.Name: ProjTerm
Formula.Notes: Term of projection in months from policy commencement
Formula.Value: 'Projection term from outset (in months) 'For WOL this is calculated as the time until the appropriate lives reach the max age in the mortality table 'For other products this is set to the minimum of the Input variable Term * 12 and the max age in mortality table Return Term_w

Formula.Name: PropIF_e
Formula.Notes: Proportion of policies still in force at the end of month t (after all claims and lapses)
Formula.Value:
'Proportion still in force at the end of month t 'Assume policy is still in force at later of policy commencement and valuation date If t <= Max(0, PeriodIF()) Then Return 1
Return PropIF_e(t - 1) - NumNatDeaths(t) - NumAccDeaths(t) - NumLapses(t) - NumCancels(t) - NumNTU(t)

Formula.Name: RFRAnnNom
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else If RUN_TYPE = "OPN" Then Return Tbl_FwdNom.Value(ValMnth(t), START_DT) / 100 Else If RUN_TYPE = "CLS" Then Return Tbl_FwdNom.Value(ValMnth(t), VALN_DT) / 100 End If End If

Formula.Name: RFRAnnReal
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else If RUN_TYPE = "OPN" Then Return Tbl_FwdReal.Value(ValMnth(t), START_DT) / 100 Else If RUN_TYPE = "CLS" Then Return Tbl_FwdReal.Value(ValMnth(t), VALN_DT) / 100 End If End If

Formula.Name: RIAccDeathClaim
Formula.Value: Return NumAccDeaths(t) * RIBenTotal()

Formula.Name: RIBenTotal
Formula.Value: Return RI_T1_SA + RI_T2_SA

Formula.Name: RIClaimRec_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (RIClaimRec_PV_e(t + 1) + RIClaimsRec(t + 1)) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: RIClaimsRec
Formula.Value: If Pol_Year(t) > RPR_CONTR_BND_1 Then Return 0 Else Return RIClaimsRecPrePS(t) End If

Formula.Name: RIClaimsRecPrePS
Formula.Value: Return RINatDeathClaim(t) + RIAccDeathClaim(t)

Formula.Name: RINatDeathClaim
Formula.Value: Return NumNatDeaths(t) * RIBenTotal()

Formula.Name: RINetCF
Formula.Value: Return RIPremOutgo(t) - RIClaimsRec(t)

Formula.Name: RIPremOutgo
Formula.Value: If t < PeriodIF() Or Pol_Year(t) > RPR_CONTR_BND_1 Then Return 0 Else Return RIPrmPrePS(t) - RIProfitShare(t) End If

Formula.Name: RIPrem_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) of all death claims paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return (RIPrem_PV_e(t + 1) + RIPremOutgo(t + 1)) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1)

Formula.Name: RIPrmPrePS
Formula.Value: If t > 0 Then Return RIBenTotal() * (1 - (1 - AnnRIRate(t)) ^ (1 / 12)) * PropIF_e(t - 1) Return 0

Formula.Name: RIPrmRate
Formula.Value:
Dim RILU As String Dim RIPrmRFScl As Double Dim RIPrmRatelocal As Double Dim SelectLU As String Dim RISelectBand As String
If t <= Max(PeriodIF(), 0) Then Return 0
SelectLU = String.Concat(SM_Mortality_Life1.SEX, SM_Mortality_Life1.SMK)
If DurIF(t) <= Tbl_RISelectBands.Value(SelectLU, 1) Then RISelectBand = "1" Else RISelectBand = "ultimate" End If
RILU = String.Concat(SM_Mortality_Life1.SEX, SM_Mortality_Life1.SMK, SM_Mortality_Life1.AgeLast(t).ToString())
RIPrmRFScl = Tbl_RIRFRskScl.Value(SM_Mortality_Life1.RF_RSK) / 100 RIPrmRatelocal = Math.Min(Tbl_RIPrm.Value(RILU, RISelectBand), 1)
Return Math.Min(RIPrmRFScl * RIPrmRatelocal, 1)

Formula.Name: RIProfitShare
Formula.Value: If Pol_Year(t) > RPR_CONTR_BND_1 Or Pol_Year(t) <= RPR_CONTR_BND Then Return 0 Else Return Math.Max((RIPrmPrePS(t) * (1 - (RPR_EXP_PROF_PC / 100)) - RIClaimsRec(t)) * RPR_PROF_PC / 100, 0) End If

Formula.Name: RenExpTotal
Formula.Value: If t < Term_w Then If ValMnth(t) = 0 Then Return 0 Else Return (ExpAcq(t) + ExpRenMain(t) + ExpPremRec(t)) * PropIF_e(t - 1) End If End If

Formula.Name: Res_e
Formula.Notes: Reserve at end of month t
Formula.Value:
'Calculate reserve at the end of month t
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return NatDthBen_PV_e(t) + AccDthBen_PV_e(t) + TotExp_PV_e(t) + NBPremWOP_PV_e(t) - Prem_PV_e(t) - PremRec_PV_e(t)

Formula.Name: SeasonalCancelAdj
Formula.Value: Return Tbl_ExitSeasonAdj.Value(ValDate.AddMonths(ValMnth(t)).Month, "CNL")

Formula.Name: SeasonalLapseAdj
Formula.Value: Return Tbl_ExitSeasonAdj.Value(ValDate.AddMonths(ValMnth(t)).Month, "LPS")

Formula.Name: TotExp_PV_e
Formula.Notes: Present value (at end of month t) for all expenses paid from month t+1 onwards
Formula.Value:
'Present Value at the end of month t of all expenses paid from month t+1 onwards
If t = ProjTerm() Then Return 0
Return TotExp_PV_e(t + 1) * DiscFac_mnth(t + 1) + CFSoM(t+1)

Formula.Name: ValMnth
Formula.Notes: Number of months since valuation date
Formula.Value: '<Attributes(CalcOnce:=True)> Return t - PeriodIF()

Formula.Name: ValYr
Formula.Notes: Year of valuation, first 12 months immediately following the valuation date have ValnYear of 1
Formula.Value: '<Attributes(CalcOnce:=True)> If ValMnth(t) < 0 Then Return CInt(Fix((ValMnth(t) - 11) / 12)) Else Return CInt(Fix((ValMnth(t) + 11) / 12)) End If
